(40, 25, 4, 19, 45, 7, 7, 'oil in their vessels', 'Connection of Oil and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the significance of oil as a symbol of divine favor and joy. Both passages emphasize the importance of being prepared and righteous, as seen in the wise taking oil and God anointing with the oil of gladness.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 4, 38, 4, 2, 3, 'oil in their vessels with their lamps', 'Connection of Oil and Lamps', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of lamps and oil, symbolizing readiness and illumination. The wise in Matthew prepare with oil for their lamps, while Zechariah describes a candlestick with lamps fed by olive trees, suggesting a source of sustenance and light.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 4, 48, 5, 22, 23, 'the wise took oil', 'Connection of Preparedness and Virtue', 'This connection highlights the importance of being prepared, as seen in the wise taking oil for their lamps, which parallels the cultivation of virtues like love and faith in Galatians. Both passages emphasize the necessity of readiness and spiritual fruitfulness in one''s life.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 5, 35, 2, 3, 3, NULL, 'Waiting and Vigilance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of waiting during a period of delay. In Matthew, the bridegroom''s tarrying leads to slumber, while Habakkuk encourages waiting for the vision despite its delay.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
