(40, 25, 5, 61, 3, 4, 9, 'they all slumbered and slept', 'Connection of Waiting and Sleep', 'Both passages emphasize a period of waiting and the state of being asleep. In Matthew, the bridegroom''s delay leads to slumber, while in 2 Peter, the question of the Lord''s coming reflects a sense of complacency among people.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
