(40, 25, 5, 42, 20, 9, 9, 'tarried', 'Delay and Vigilance Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of waiting and vigilance in both passages. In Matthew, the bridegroom''s delay leads to slumber, while in Luke, the man''s long absence emphasizes the need for the husbandmen to remain attentive.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 5, 40, 25, 19, 19, 'tarried', 'Delay and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of waiting and the eventual return of the master. Both passages emphasize a period of delay before reckoning occurs.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 5, 41, 14, 37, 38, 'slumbered and slept', 'Sleep and Vigilance Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of sleep and the call to vigilance in both passages. In Matthew, the bridegroom''s delay leads to slumber, while in Mark, Jesus admonishes Peter for sleeping instead of staying awake to pray.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(40, 25, 6, 61, 3, 10, 10, 'the bridegroom cometh', 'The Coming of the Bridegroom', 'This connection highlights the imminent arrival of the bridegroom in Matthew and the unexpected coming of the day of the Lord in 2 Peter. Both passages emphasize a sudden and significant event that requires readiness and alertness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
